      "business_constraints": {
        "assistant_drafted_requirements_count": 10,
        "assistant_drafted_requirements_summary": "Expose a governed Jira capability surface instead of raw Jira operations: The product shall present business-facing Jira capabilities for bounded context lookup, issue and comment preparation, governed change requests, and release-note preparation. It shall not expose raw Jira REST, MCP operations, raw Jira tools, or direct raw JQL access to agents or end users.\nReturn bounded, actor-visible Jira context for read flows: The product shall support bounded Jira read capabilities for backlog context search and single-issue context retrieval. Read results must be limited to actor-visible fields and bounded context, including optional comments and history where allowed, and must avoid unbounded issue export.\nRequire clarification for missing, ambiguous, or unresolved required inputs: For governed Jira capabilities, the product shall require clarification when required inputs are missing, ambiguous, or unresolved through backend catalogs. It shall not guess project keys, issue references, statuses, assignees, sprint targets, releases, or link types.\nSupport preview-only preparation for issue and comment creation flows: The product shall support preview preparation flows for incident bugs, stories, subtasks, and customer escalation comments. These flows must produce drafts or previews for review without directly creating Jira issues or posting comments as part of the initial request.\nGate Jira-changing requests behind explicit approval boundaries: The product shall support governed request flows for workflow transitions, sprint moves, assignee changes, and issue links. These flows must stop at an approval boundary when policy requires it, returning a preview of the intended change and the stated business reason before any execution occurs.\nDeny unsafe or out-of-policy Jira access explicitly: The product shall explicitly deny requests for raw Jira tool access, raw JQL exposure, unrestricted export, or other out-of-policy operations. Denial responses should be intentional and explain that only governed capabilities are available.\nProduce audit evidence for governed reads, previews, approvals, and denials: The product shall preserve audit evidence for governed Jira interactions, including what capability was invoked, what bounded scope or target was requested, whether the result was a read, clarification, preview, approval stop, or denial, and enough context for later reviewer inspection.\nPrepare release notes from bounded Jira issue context without publishing: The product shall support release-note preparation from bounded Jira issue and release context. It must generate draft release notes for supported audiences without publishing externally and without mutating Jira.\nResolve business references through governed Jira catalogs: The product shall resolve business references such as projects, issues, workflow statuses, sprints, assignees, releases, components, and issue link types through governed backend resolution rather than freeform execution. When resolution fails or is ambiguous, the system must clarify or deny according to policy.\nApply role-aware governance across bounded reads, change requests, and audit review: The product shall support distinct actor postures for triage, delivery coordination, release preparation, change approval, and audit review. Permissions must distinguish bounded access, approval-required actions, direct audit review access where intended, and denied governance-control access for non-review actors."
      }
    }
  },
